## How to Spawn Subagents (read this first)

The mechanics of spawning subagents, the full model roster, and the multi-model rules live in **`subagents.mdc`**. Read it before this protocol. The short version:

- Every "spawn a subagent" call uses the Task tool with `model` set EXPLICITLY (never omit it -- omitting it runs on your own model and kills multi-model coverage).
- If a slug gets rejected, pick another valid one the tool returns. **Never drop the `model` param and silently fall back to your own model.**
- When you spawn several subagents for the same job, use **different model families** -- never the same slug twice for the same job. Diversity beats power; cheap models from different families are fine.

Whenever this file names specific slugs below (e.g. `claude-opus-4-8-thinking-xhigh`, `gpt-5.5-extra-high`), they're examples from the `subagents.mdc` roster -- swap in whatever valid slugs give you family diversity.

