## Phase 5: Final Review

This review answers two questions: **(1) Did every feature survive? (2) Was it actually built better?** It is not a code-quality-only review, and it is not a pixel-match review. The review here is **exhaustive and looped** -- it does not stop until a clean pass exists. The biggest past failures (an entire page missing, ~75% of features dropped) all slipped through because the final review SAMPLED instead of enumerating, and ran only once.

### Step 0: Build the reconciliation ledger FIRST (no sampling, ever)

Before any subjective review, build a mechanical ledger -- this is the gate that makes a silently-dropped feature impossible:

1. **Route diff.** List every route in the inventory's route manifest. Next to each, write the new app's matching route and whether it loads in the running app (open it -- not from code). Every old route must have a working new route. A blank or missing row here is exactly the "whole page never built" failure.
2. **Inventory ID ledger.** Go through EVERY ID in FEATURE-INVENTORY.md -- all of them, in order, none skipped. For each, record: built? (which file) and verified-in-running-app? (PRESENT / PARTIAL / STUB / MISSING, with evidence -- the route you opened and what you clicked). "Enumerate every line" is mandatory; "spot-checked a few pages and it looked fine" is the failure mode that lost the order builder.

Write this ledger into **REBUILD-COMPLETION-REPORT.md**. If you cannot account for an ID, it is MISSING, not "probably fine."

### Step 1: Running-app review

Using the ledger, go through every screen in the running app:

- **Feature completeness (the keep list):** every feature/control from the inventory is walked -- not a sample. Mark each PRESENT / PARTIAL / STUB / MISSING. A screen fails if anything is less than PRESENT and functional.
- **Structural improvement (the to-fix list):** confirm each fix from the inventory/plan was applied -- misplaced things moved, related things grouped, clashing interactions resolved.
- **Layout quality:** click through it. Does the CSS line up? Is it consistent across the app? Does it work at different screen widths? No leftover "stack of cards" messiness.

Verifying from code review alone is NOT allowed. Run it, click it.

### Step 2: Multi-model audit (looped until clean)

Spawn 2 subagents on different premier families (e.g. `claude-opus-4-8-thinking-xhigh` and `gpt-5.5-extra-high`; rotate families per `subagents.mdc`). Each gets the finished codebase, the full FEATURE-INVENTORY.md (route manifest + every ID + the to-fix list), and the reference screenshots.

Each subagent prompt:
> "Compare this finished app against the FEATURE-INVENTORY.md below. Go through EVERY route in the manifest and EVERY numbered ID -- all of them, no sampling. (1) ROUTE COVERAGE: for each route, does a working equivalent exist in the new app? (2) FEATURE COMPLETENESS: for every ID (buttons, dialogs, forms, table columns, filters, import/export, row actions, bulk actions), mark PRESENT / PARTIAL / STUB / MISSING with evidence -- nothing may be dropped. (3) STRUCTURAL FIXES: confirm each to-fix item was actually addressed. (4) Was anything added that wasn't in scope? (5) Is the layout/CSS clean, consistent, and coherent? Don't just check that it compiles -- check each feature is wired and functional. Return a per-ID table; flag anything you could not verify as MISSING."

### Step 3: The review LOOP -- fix, then re-review until zero findings

This is a cycle, not a single pass (the user has asked for this explicitly):

1. Collect both audits + your running-app ledger.
2. Fix EVERY finding -- every MISSING/PARTIAL/STUB feature, every unaddressed to-fix item.
3. Spawn a **fresh** review subagent (a model that has NOT reviewed this work yet -- a new family, no prior context, so it can't rubber-stamp) and have it re-run the full enumerated check.
4. Repeat 2-3 until a review pass returns **zero findings**. One clean pass on fresh eyes is required before the rebuild can be called done.

### Step 4: Done gate

The rebuild is done ONLY when ALL of these are true. If any is false, it is not done -- keep working:

- [ ] Every route in the manifest has a working new-app route (route diff fully green).
- [ ] Every inventory ID is PRESENT and functional in the running app (ledger fully green -- no PARTIAL/STUB/MISSING).
- [ ] Every to-fix item is addressed (or explicitly deferred with the user's OK).
- [ ] The most recent review pass came back with zero findings, on a fresh/different model.
- [ ] The deploy is green per `deploy-awareness.mdc` (builds verified, not assumed).

The rebuild is done when every feature works and the app is built right -- not when it compiles, not when it looks like the old one, and not after a single review.
